        "type": "italics",
        "tokens": [
         {
          "text": "hu haya koisev",
          "type": "text"
         }
        ]
       },
       {
        "text": ") meaning “he used to write” or “he used to be writing.”",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "If you wanted to say “he wrote,” i.e. a one-time past event instead of an ongoing past event, you would just use the regular ",
        "type": "text"
